question.text: Egg coffee here trully tastes good, doesn't it? I've heard a lot about this coffee shop. Is it too crowded? Do I have to wait for a table when I come?

answer.text: At Tonkin Specialty Coffee, the allure of our egg coffee extends far beyond its delightful taste. Crafted from fresh egg, cream, and Fine Robusta coffee, this specialty beverage embodies a harmonious blend of flavors that tantalize the palate. Our commitment to sourcing high-quality ingredients ensures that each sip delivers a rich and satisfying experience. While our signature egg coffee has garnered praise from countless patrons, it's important to acknowledge the diverse array of egg coffee recipes found throughout Ho Chi Minh City. Here at Tonkin Specialty Coffee, we embrace this variety, encouraging our customers to explore and savor the unique flavors offered by different establishments. Furthermore, our satisfaction guarantee sets us apart. If, for any reason, you find yourself dissatisfied with your egg coffee experience, we offer a 100% refund. This commitment to customer satisfaction underscores our confidence in the quality of our products and service.

most_relevant.description: It was a good find and close to Ben Thanh market which is a populat place. You have to go inside a narrow corridor and go upstairs to find this hidden gem. Salted Caramel Coffee is good and lives up to its title of being the best seller. Egg coffee, another best seller, is a novelty too and it is also good. My only comment for the egg coffee is it’s more of a dessert than a coffee drink. The food is good but not really a novelty. I both love the salted egg croissant and their pork belly baguette but it is not anything new. A good partner to coffee though especially if you want to take your brunch first before going around the city.

rated as the best egg coffee in hcm and it lived up to the hype!

sweet egg creme compliments the espresso well...

salt coffee is also supposed to be another best seller but it tastes rly similar to egg coffee - the salt creme is not very unique it tastes like the foam they put on bubble teas. just get the egg coffee for a true viet experience

salted egg croissant was pretty good. melty salted egg lava oozed out of the pastry! but as singaporean we do have better viennoiseries in sg in terms of croissant quality and salted egg as a flavour is kinda passe. but good for tourists who may not have experienced salted egg flavours as much

Amazing egg coffee. I got mine with an extra shot and my wife got one with the single shot. Both were delicious. I also highly recommended the egg coffee croissant. The salted coffee was good, but a little salty for our taste (and yes, I have had many salted coffees in Vietnam before).

the most incredible egg coffee i have EVER had. it was insane i am still thinking about it to this day, 5 weeks in vietnam and this coffee blew it out of the water. the creaminess of the coffee plus the actual taste was perfect. we also got the salted croissant in the combo and it was so yummy. the staff was super nice, the atmosphere was great and has overflow rooms with strong ac. will definitely come back during my next time in hcmc! 10/10

Popped in with some friends for coffee after haggling in the market. It is located along a narrow corridor from the street and then upstairs, so not somewhere you'd necessarily notice in passing.  The coffee was delicious and beautifully presented. There was plenty of choice of drinks, and I had their own blend which was delicious.
Great service, and when we left, we were all given a little origami package with a cookie inside. Highly recommend you try this out.

The hospitality here is truly exceptional! From the moment you step in, you’re warmly welcomed and asked whether you prefer a smoking or non-smoking area before being shown to your seat. The staff is incredibly attentive, promptly bringing you the menu and suggesting their top picks. They even serve you a delightful iced tea—I’m not sure what it’s made from, but it has a floral touch and tastes absolutely amazing! I also tried the egg coffee, and I can’t even begin to explain how incredible it is—Masya Allah! The combination of friendly service, a cozy atmosphere, and such unique, flavorful drinks completely made my day. If you’re looking for a peaceful spot to enjoy your early afternoon amidst lush greenery, this place is an absolute gem!

Everything goes smoothly. Try the combo « banhmi+coffee », it is a very good start for your journey. Really a hidden gem. You need to get into a narrow hall to go upstairs. Give them some time to brew your coffee. And above all, enjoy the slow life ..

The salted coffee here is amazing, seriously one of the best I’ve had. The salted egg croissant is just next level – the filling is super soft and tasty. The atmosphere is really nice, even though it’s full, it still feels peaceful and not too noisy. The interior is cool too, makes the place even better. Definitely worth a visit

I was in this coffee shop a few days ago, it is located in District 1, near the Cathedral of Our Lady of Saigon. Below I list the significant points of this coffee bar, in the first point I will write the fundamental thing that is how the coffee ☕️ drinks 🥤 and the food is, so that you will not waste time reading my novel 😜:

COFFEE TEA JUICES FOOD:
I ordered a coffee ☕️ and two juices and one free because the service guys are good but they need to pay more attention to the "details". However, apart from this mix-up I have to say that the coffee is good but the juices were really the best and for me this place is a YES 👌.

PRICE:
The price is not expensive and is average for places in District 1.

EXTERNAL ENVIRONMENT:
As I said, it is located in District 1, near the cathedral and from here, once you have drunk your coffee ☕️ or some other drink, you can move on foot and reach the attractions of District 1 in a few minutes. However, for those who know HCM, it is a chaotic city, there is always a casino, so it is not surprising that as soon as you leave the place you hear a mess of sounds, smells and an army of scooters 🛵 parked right at the door!

INTERIOR ENVIRONMENT:
As soon as you see the facade of the entrance to the coffee shop, you will immediately see that this place has style compared to those around it. Then just see the movement of people entering and leaving the place to understand that you are in the right place. When you enter, the place is not very big, but it is on two floors and the upper floor is larger, the furnishings are cute retro objects and books 📕 that give you a sense of a place of artists and poets, there is a glass window that overlooks the street and the scooters 🛵 😀.

ATMOSPHERE:
Let's start by saying that the atmosphere is youthful, friendly and relaxing. Youthful because the service is managed by young people, the customers are boys and girls and you can feel the positive energy of the kids. This place is trendy and also serves as a photo set, in fact many girls and boys come to this place to take photos and it is interesting to watch them while they pose, how "professional" they are in taking each photo shot 📸 and double checking that the photo is perfect in every detail, for this reason alone I would come to this place every day in addition to having a coffee also to watch these young people who put a lot of passion even in a simple photo!

SERVICE:
As written at the beginning, the service is carried out by young people, you can see their vivacity, energy, positivity, enthusiasm and cheerfulness. Apart from a mix-up that occurred with a fruit juice, which they remedied immediately and here you can see their desire to improve on the mistake made, they immediately apologized and offered a new fruit juice. They are young people and you can see that they put effort, passion into what they do because they want the customer when he leaves the place satisfied and wants to return to their place because he had a good time.

TO IMPROVE:
A piece of advice when I arrived at the place there was no more pastry shop 🥐 🍰🧁 it's a shame, a solution should be found so that it is always possible to have it, because there are cultures like mine (Italian) but also our French cousins ​​it is in their culture that together with a good coffee ☕️ it must be accompanied by a croissant or a pastry.
Another tip the bathroom door please 🙏 fix it. Thanks 😊

The best coffee shop. I went to many of them during my vacations in Saigon but in Choice is just the best coffee ever. Best vibe! Best staff: thank u so much guys u made for me tastiest vietnamese coffee and being so smiling and cute, and friendly! I went to Choice every day and tried all coffee menu, but iced coconut and salted cream coffee - my fave! Seriously the best coffee in my life😍 I’m dreaming come back to Saigon and to Choice cafe and have a glass of my best vietnamese coffee again😍

Very nice coffee and tea shop (with great smoothies as well) close to the Opera House.  Excellent friendly service makes it an easy choice come back whenever I’m in Saigon.  Also has both indoor AC seating and a few seats outside as well for those that want to people watch.

I had a coconut coffee. The table moved and some of the coffee spilled. They asked me if I wanted another one and I said yes expecting they would just poor it into another cup.

The girl working was so insistent on making me a whole new cup and was very sweet.

The coffee was good and I would come here again, but 5 stars for the service.

This was our go to spot for coffee for a few days. We tried one thing and one thing only - the coconut coffee. Like the other reviews have highlighted, it’s incredible. Coffee, coconut cream and blended ice. Simple. But delicious and unlike any other “coffee” I’ve tried. Like a cross between a milk shake and coffee. Being from out of town, I was initially nervous about the ice but it’s safe and we were fine. Like a lot of good cafes and restaurants, they use factory manufactured ice.

Hana waited on us and she was so helpful and gracious. We sat out front of this quaint coffee shop just behind the Saigon Opera house on one of two cafe tables. The inside was air conditioned and had additional seating. I had the salted coffee and my wife had a hot cappuccino. These were the best coffees we have had in Saigon ( and we have tried a lot of coffee shops). The prices a very reasonable, atmosphere great and coffee irresistible. A must try

posts.description:
HOW CAN YOU FIND HOFF COFFE BREWERS? ☕

Step 1: Go to 42bis Ly Tu Trong D1. Then come inside
Step 2: Go upstairs and turn right. We're on the 1st floor. 
Step 3: Go to the end of the hallway. 
------
Since it’s located in an apartment building, Hoff knows that many of you visiting for the first time might get a bit lost wandering around.
But don’t worry! Hoff Coffee Brewers is here to guide you to the shop.

‼️ Note: If you’re visiting Hoff by motorbike, please park at Alley 40 Ly Tu Trong (Military Alley), which is just three houses away from Hoff!

Check out the photos for directions! Wishing you a wonderful day ♥️

most_relevant.description: One of the best places for coffee in Ho Chi Minh. By third wave standards it’s not bad, their latte was pretty good (7.8), milk blend was a little thick and the beans lacked full flavour. The drip coffee was not a refined as you’d like, the beans were a little over roasted. But I can really only judge it by its local peers and so it’s a great place if you’re in the city.

I visit Saigon for a short while but spent days here. The latte was so gooddd, milk steamed so well. Coffee was so smoothhh. Literally a gem for those look for great coffee not commercial one. Must try!!!!!! 😍🥳🤯
The coffee and matcha latte were tasty, not too strong. Lovely interior with many plants and a nice balcony with view of the street. They offer oat milk
It is our first time visiting Hoff. We tried the dirty matcha and hoff béo matcha. The drinks were great. The place was really quiet and cozy. We even played around with the lego pieces on our table.

You must come try this coconut coffee! It was so delicious. A nice little space that’s a bit difficult to find, go into the alley and up the stairs, you will see signs.

Staff are friendly and there is a little terrace overlooking the street which is lovely to enjoy coffee on.

Very nice place (a bit difficult to find though). The coffee and desserts are really good! We had a salted caramel latte (hot),  a Vietnamese coffee with fresh and condensed milk (cold) and a cinnamon roll.
This Hoff matcha cafe was amazing !!! You have to try it. Also the place is quite hidden in a building so it makes it even more special. Loved this place !!!!

a very cute spot with the friendliest staff. if you're not getting iced coffee though, which they're known for, you really have to tell you want your coffee hot not lukewarm. besides that it was amazing

most_relevant.description: Libra Coffee and Bar offers a perfect blend of a cozy café by day and a lively bar by night. The warm, rustic décor creates an inviting atmosphere ideal for relaxing with a cup of coffee or enjoying a casual drink with friends. Their coffee is rich and flavorful, made from well-sourced beans, while their cocktail menu is creative and refreshing. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring a pleasant experience whether you're stopping by for a quick coffee or staying for an evening drink. Libra is a versatile spot that's perfect for both daytime relaxation and evening socializing.

After 2 weeks of being served vietnamese coffee with passion and dedication, this is by far my worst coffee place experience and I am very disappointed.
The iced coffee is served with 2 huge chunks of ice, which makes it a challenge to take a sip without having the ice bump into your face.
I understand they also do movie nights and project them on the wall. But we were there at least 1h before that and out of a sudden they started projecting their Spotify directly in our faces as we happened to sit at the table next to the movie screen. No warning, no sorry, no nothing.
Then the guy behind the counter was continuously typing on his phone and sending messages with loud beeping sounds on, which were even louder than the background music.
Needless to say that we were not served any tea from the house, which is not a must from my side, but everywhere we had a coffee in Vietnam we also were served some tea before being brought the order.

Discovered today and what a joy! Outstanding coffee. Wonderful service. Great environment for a meeting that went nearly 5 hours. And then a nice couple of drinks to close out the day. Really, really recommend you discover and enjoy.

Very cute, chill and intimate place to study, work or have a break from the busy city!

Love that the place is a bit on the side. Obviously the team make a lot of efforts for the decoration!

Staff is welcoming and very helpful. We troubled them a bit with seats since we came at different time  They had so many different coffee, had the Libra cafe. Waouhhh! Was very tasty. Thank you guys!

Stopped in for a drink after picking up our laundry. I had a fantastic Negroni and my wife had a berry infused gin and tonic. Both were absolutely delicious and we loved sitting outside watching a part of the world go by. The young lady that served us was super attentive and polite. We hope to get back there before we leave.

Had such pleasant experience there at the cafe. Staff spoke English, showed the best attitude and was extremely attentive. Reliable wifi plus greenary atmosphere makes it perfect for working and relaxing. Will come back for more! Happy to recommend!

The space is not so big, but the drinks are very good and reasonably priced for the quality. I tried their cookie and they reheat it before bringing it to you, which is nice. The vibe is chilling and nice here as well.

Nestled in the heart of District 1, Libra Coffee and Bar is a highly-rated gem that offers a serene escape from the bustling city. This charming café boasts a cozy indoor setting complemented by a pleasant covered outdoor area. Book lovers will appreciate the small library, adding to the café's tranquil ambiance ideal for working or reading.

The menu features a range of regular coffee options, including local favorites, with the White Coffee standing out as a delightful choice. Tea enthusiasts will find interesting selections to explore as well. While the food offerings are limited, the small selection of pastries, primarily croissants, pairs nicely with the beverages.

With WiFi available, Libra Coffee and Bar caters to both leisure seekers and remote workers. Its combination of a relaxing atmosphere, quality drinks, and convenient location makes it a highly recommended spot for locals and tourists alike in Ho Chi Minh City.

most_relevant.description: Had breakfast around 9:30am and was about 70% full. Remote working crowd and some breakfast goers too. Quick service and delicious food. Plus the iced tea and coffee were fantastic. Really enjoyed my meal and would absolutely come back. Prices were very good. To find the place go up 2 flights from an unassuming door on the street.

A quiet work place hidden in district one, you need to find the entrance and take steps to 2nd floor.
Spacious and quiet place, plugs at window seats.
Wouldn’t say the food was great but the coffee is good. There are also tea options.

This cafe is a real gem! Its industrial decor fits the voluminous space very well, and the art on the walls lends it an organic and artistic feel.

The coffees we had were expertly crafted and lacked no creativity, and the service was knowledgeable, forthcoming, swift, and friendly. Especially Trung stood out, with whom we had a pleasant conversation and who looked after us very well.

The premises are suited for a quiet coffee with a book, for a date with friends, or for co-working as there is plenty of space, power points as a decent wifi, and an abundance of natural light to make it suited for prolonged periods.

The building itself is quite 'smudgy and old' which adds tons of charm to entering and walking up the dark rectangular staircase. It offers lots of IG photo ops ; ) . If you are carrying an upright piano or a load of suitcases, climbing the stairs to the cafe may be a bit of a chore, but otherwise its all part of the experience and fun, and at the end of the climb you're rewarded with a superb cafe!

All in all I highly recommend this 5* coffee!

This establishment is undeniably bustling, offering a lively atmosphere that may appeal to those seeking a vibrant social environment.

While the food and coffee are satisfactory, and the service is adequate, the overall ambiance did not align with my personal preferences.
I found the space overly crowded and noisy, which made it less conducive to relaxation or focused work—a priority for someone with a nomadic lifestyle. Consequently, I opted to stay only briefly, just long enough to enjoy a quick coffee.

While the energetic, open social vibe may suit many, it ultimately wasn’t the right fit for me.

Pros
- Fast and friendly service
- Cappuccino was hot and the consistency of the milk was great
- Eggs Benedict tested very good. The asparagus as an ingredient toke a bit of time getting used to it, but in the end it was a good combination overall.

Cons
- The entrance is a bit hard to find, but there is a sign on the street next to the entrance. It looks like the entry of a normal house (what it is). Then you have to go up 2 floors and you’re there.

Food and cafe here’s always amazing. I love the vibe, the quality of food and cafe, the space filled with paintings (they renew them every several months).
**They also do free refill water here. Highly recommended!
***Price for one: ~200k if you have only one dish. <300k if you have food and coffee. >300k if you have dessert also.

A bit on the pricier side but the vibes make up for it lol Somehow it’s giving quaint downtown new work vibes, it’s a good place to work/study. Definitely a place you could romanticize your life in 😆🤎
great place to get work done, lots of expats/tourists. spacious and comfortable except maybe the chairs. the omelette with pancetta (i think?) was really good, they have card payment

most_relevant.description:
Great experience and taste! I got the coffee they prepare for you with fire and the egg coffee. Both were great!

Loved the experience, the taste, and the baristas were friendly and explained everything to me. Also spoke English so was able to communicate with them.

A little hard to find, so just go up the stairs by the corner.

I would definitely return!

Khang is the coffee person you need to know if you're visiting Ho Chi Minh. He will tell you so much about the Vietnamese coffee. Specialty coffee & the traditional Vietnamese Coffee Phin was phenomenal. Best service and roasting experience.

Wow! This was such a unique and fascinating experience. Egg coffee was delicious and I was told how to properly drink it. I’ve been in Vietnam for over a month now and this is the first time I’ve been told how to drink it properly! I also had a croissant and it was perfectly flaky and crispy and went very well with my coffee. My boyfriend had a personalized coffee which was super cool! The barista was very kind and knowledgeable and spoke very good English. She is a true coffee scientist!
FYI: This place was a bit tricky to find, if you follow google maps and feel confused, look for the stairs at the end of the building, this place is on the 2nd floor. You won’t regret coming here! I wish this place had been my first Vietnamese coffee experience.

Thank you very much! 💝

A truly fantastic experience. From the moment you walk in you know it’s going to be good! The staff go above and beyond to take you through every step and share the unique experience of Vietnamese coffee with you. I would highly recommend to anyone!

currently the temperature in HCMC is 35degC and I found a comfortable place to drink coffee. The composition of 70% Arabica and 30% Robusta with the right roasting really relieved my desire to enjoy coffee this afternoon.

Attracted by FB Ads, the atmosphere is great, you can chill the whole afternoon in the shop for work or studying.
They can customize the coffee flavor base on your preference, but personally don’t expect that much as long as the taste is good.
They recommend egg coffee and coffee phin for newbies, I tried coffee phin, its taste a little bit strong and bitter for me, doesn’t like that much.
They lets you enjoy 50 ml in-house and bring home a small bottle for cool drink. Total is 149k

Outstanding egg coffee! Love the Phin coffee and quite an experience watching the process. And the citrus coffee…so good cold. And the mocha coffee is so chocolatey. All drinks except egg coffee is customised to individual preference.
Lots of love put into the art of coffee! Very knowledgeable, friendly and unpretentious barista. We love the coffee so much we bought 5 bags home. A X-factor experience!

I had the most amazing experience here! Kenny is a master at his craft. It was the best coffee I've ever tasted and to see him do his work in front of you is really special. I thoroughly enjoyed my experience and when I return I will come back again for this wonderful coffee.Thank you Kenny, you are a master of this. You can also buy a bag of the coffee he personalized for you here. 😊

most_relevant.description:
Cafe Review: A French Gem in the Heart of the Backpacker Jungle

Tucked away in the middle of a rather rough-and-ready backpacker hub, this charming breakfast spot is a total surprise. Step inside, and it’s like walking into a little slice of Paris — cozy, inviting, and full of delicious French-style breakfast options. Think buttery croissants, creamy scrambled eggs, and rich coffee that actually hits the spot.

What really sets this place apart, though, is the staff. They’re warm, genuinely friendly, and impressively attentive — a perfect balance of polite and efficient. There’s a certain assertiveness to how they handle the service, which is actually quite refreshing. It’s clear they know what they’re doing, and they do it well.

Definitely worth the stop — whether you’re a weary traveler or just someone craving a proper breakfast in an unexpected corner of the city.

Absolutely amazing! Staff are so nice, helpful, friendly and very kind, especially Chi, huge shoutout to her for the best service ever. We came as family of 5 and they always had a table for us, service was very quick and food so delicious. The breakfast combo is such a great deal! I recommend for everyone to go there, it will be a highlight of your trip and you will not regret it! Thanks for everything guys, continue spreading kindness! May you have all the best customers 🥳💕

This is a small cafe with good air conditioning. If you are looking to get simple breakfast in a nice quiet, cool facility, this is the place. The customer service is great, I’ve been here a few times and the lady always says “very nice to see you again!” It has a very homely feel to it.

I ordered the combo every time. Basically, you get a choice of eggs with bread, crepe, drink (coffee, tea, juice), and a dessert choice. I get the omelette, banana and chocolate crepe, pineapple juice, with fruits. The portions aren’t huge but there is a lot of flavour in the eggs. I feel as though the last time I went there, they gave me a larger portion though lol.

Like I said, super kid people, simple breakfast, nice ac. Can’t go wrong coming here.

On a hot and humid April Saigon morning, this cafe was a very welcoming retreat for a special breakfast.  After spending a few days in a very noisy and chaotic city, this cafe provided an atmosphere of calmness, peaceful, and relaxing experience. The hostess was friendly and cheerful. The food and coffee were amazing and beautifully presented.  Could not have asked for a better place.  Thank you, Chez Mimosa Cafe & Breakfast! 🙏🏻

This place was a welcome break from eating more traditional street food in the open air. Walking into the airconditioning was an escape from the oppressive heat and noise of Ho Chi Minh's streets. Right outside the door and in the alley nearby were hawkers selling fruit and banh mi, while inside we had fruit and banh mi with coffee and crepes. We had 2 combos, egg and bread and Vietnamese bread plus banana crepes with chocolate, coffee and fresh fruit for VND125K each. With 2 extra drinks added all 4 of us had something delicious to eat. Along with the incredible food we had magnificent, friendly service with food delivered quickly.

What an amazing & friendly place. The staff are so attentive &
speak english. The food is freshly cooked & delicious. I particualy love the fresh yogurt that they make daily. If you are looking for breakfast then give this place a try, you wont be disappointed!!

Most gorgeous cafe in busy Ho Chi Minh City, the staff are so sweet and friendly, and happy to accommodate any request.
The food was delicious and great value for money.
The coffee was also great.
We couldn't fault it so went back the next day :)

Had a wonderful experience! Walked in and was greeted right away. She was very patient and accommodating. Everything was delelicious and came out in a timely manner. Additionally, everything was freshly made! I highly recommend coming here for your breakfast run!

most_relevant.description: one of my favorite coffee spots in Saigon!!! the atmosphere, the drink, the politeness of the staffs, everything are perfect. i love blended matcha drink and bánh trứng muối cay, so yummy and worth the kinda high prices. i always feel so comfortable and relaxed when i sit here, talking to my friends or just studying alone. the place is not much decorated like other "high-priced" coffee shops, but you'll definitely feel like home here.
In my opinion, the best coffee I have had in Vietnam. I had a simple hot Americano. Excellent! Sadly, I came here to buy beans, but they had sold out. A calm place to sit and work.
The salt cream matcha was amazing. Went to this cafe everyday while we were in HCM. Digital nomad friendly and very good service.

Epic Coffee Roaster is a standout café for true coffee enthusiasts. Known for their specialty roasts, the café offers a range of coffee beans sourced from various regions, all roasted to perfection in-house. The minimalist, cozy interior provides a relaxed vibe, perfect for both casual coffee dates or focused work sessions. Their espresso-based drinks are smooth and well-balanced, while pour-over options highlight the distinct flavors of each roast. The knowledgeable staff are passionate about coffee and are always eager to share recommendations. For anyone looking to explore quality coffee in a calm setting, Epic Coffee Roaster is the place to be.

The cold brew here is very tasty! IT IS VERY COMFORTABLE TO SIT AND WORK HERE, a huge plus compared to other places is that quiet music plays only on the first floor, not disturbing people on the second. A nice courtyard. The waiter with long hair is extremely polite, will change your water, smiles pleasantly. As for drinks: I can’t recommend Moka (it’s good for those with a sweet tooth), but the hot Latte and spicy cold brew are amazing. Clean, nice light.

We had our first coffee in Vietnam at Epic Coffee, and are we blown away by the taste or what? The roast is so well done. I got clear notes even in an iced almond latte. The service was polite and with pretty smiles. Loved this place.

It's a nice coffee shop with bare minimalist decor. They have seating at ground floor and upper floor as well as outdoor for those who smoke. The seat not comfort but still able to sit for 1-2 hours. They have choice for single origin beans but for me the coffee is not nice for a coffee shop with roaster in the name. Look how they make an ice espresso.

Suitable for work and quite place to enjoy the coffee.
Should try the Epic espresso with condense milk here. The Ethiopia bean has a good taste and smell.

most_relevant.description: Great coffee and culture workshop. Julia taught me a lot about how to make a perfect phin filter coffee. 15% arabica beans +85% robusta beans is a really nice blend for phin filter coffee because it's strong but still has flavor nuaces. Highly recommend reserving workshops here!

Informative and amazing coffee making experience. I really appreciated Siu and Joey for helping to create the morning class. My favorite was the salted coffee. So tasty!

I also really appreciate that they recognized my lactose intolerance. They were able to offer substitutes (coconut cream and oat milk) in place of their usual dairy ingredients. Thank you!

We tried the workshop to make three Vietnamese coffees from scratch and the whole experience was incredible! Noah, our facilitator was super helpful and attentive and walked us through a short presentation going through the coffee culture in Vietnam and the independent coffee cultivators Lacaph supports. I thoroughly enjoyed the coffee making experience and was great to see a business supporting local farmers! Thanks again to Noah for a great experience and I’d highly recommend if you’re visiting HCM city.

The Vietnamese coffee workshop is one of the best experiences ive done in Vietnam! It is very well paced, interesting, and fun. Our instructor for the day was Julia, who is very friendly and knowledgeable.

Highly recommended to come here for the workshop 😍

The fun and easy coffee workshop for beginners with Sierra was amazing! Sierra did an excellent job of explaining each ingredient, the process, the story behind each coffee and the beans they use. Plus we got a cute certificate and nice discount at their cafe at the end. Thank you so much we will be back!!

I had an amazing experience with Lacaph! I took the Vietnamese Coffee and Culture class, and it was such a great way to dive into the local culture here in Saigon. Vi, our instructor, was incredibly kind and accommodating. He really took the time to make sure all of our questions were answered and taught us so well! If you're visiting Saigon, this is definitely a must-do experience. Highly recommend it!

Amazing coffee experience with LaCàph! Learned so much about Vietnamese coffee culture, tried different brews from Siu and Joey. Super friendly hosts and a beautiful space—highly recommend if you're in Vietnam!

The coffee workshop was one of the most beautiful experiences of our trip to Vietnam! Ny was a fantastic teacher and facilitator, we learnt so much about Vietnam, coffee and had access to touching stories while sipping on incredible coffee and delicious snacks. I would recommend this place and experience to anyone who is in Saigon :) plenty of shopping available too!

30/4 - Mừng ngày Giải phóng trong khoảng trời đậm hương nguyên bản

Ngày 30 tháng 4, đất nước nối liền một dải. Từ hai đầu tổ quốc, những nhịp đập từng chia đôi giờ chung một tiết tấu, hòa cùng nhau, tạo nên khúc ca thống nhất – khúc ca của những người đã sống, đã đấu tranh, và đã yêu đất mẹ bằng cả cuộc đời.

XLIII Coffee chúc bạn một ngày lễ thật trọn vẹn. Và nếu đang tìm một điểm hoà chung niềm đồng điệu, mời bạn ghé XLIII Coffee, ngồi lại bên tách cà phê nguyên bản, cùng cảm nhận sâu hơn điều đẹp đẽ ấy. Vì đôi khi, cách để ghi nhớ, nhân rộng một điều lớn lao là sự đồng cảm, sẻ chia trong từng điều nhỏ bé.

Ngày lễ này, XLIII Coffee luôn mở cửa, vẫn sẽ không phụ thu để đón những cuộc gặp gỡ đầy ý nghĩa. Hẹn bạn tại XLIII Coffee, trong hương vị tinh khôi ngày Giải phóng!

Charming specialty coffee shop :) tried the Finca Rosenheim. the coffee is not bitter unlike the usual vietnamese coffee and they dont put condensed milk so you can really taste the notes :D They also serve pastries. Really like the ambiance so chill. Light and airy place.

anh Duy is so kind to explain to us all about specialty coffees and about the coffee we ordered :)

enjoyed our time here and will definitely come back.

A Specialty Coffee Haven in Thao Dien, HCM City

This café in Thảo Điền strikes the perfect balance between modern minimalism and cozy comfort. With its airy, sunlit space, sleek wooden interiors, and a peaceful ambiance, it’s an ideal spot for both coffee aficionados and those seeking a quiet retreat. The attention to detail extends beyond the aesthetics, each cup is brewed with precision, showcasing the unique terroir of high-quality beans. Whether you're enjoying a slow pour-over or a perfectly extracted espresso, the setting enhances the experience, making every visit a moment of pure coffee appreciation.

Truly Specialty Coffee Experience in Thảo Điền, District 2, Thủ Đức City, Hồ Chí Minh City (Sài Gòn)

Specialty coffee is not just about quality beans, it’s about precision, process, and respect for the craft. Every cup reflects meticulous sourcing, careful roasting, and expert brewing, allowing the coffee’s floral complexity and refined acidity to shine. A destination for those who value coffee beyond caffeine.

Ahhh, such a cute place. I loved the tile floors, no music, and personalized service. Vinh was super-helpful in selecting out coffee experience!

However, the price is extraordinarily high — not just by Vietnam’s standard, but worldwide. Their least expensive cup is over three times the price of other great places in HCMC.

I recently visited XLIII in Thu Duc and was genuinely impressed. The place is beautifully designed with a modern and minimal aesthetic that makes it perfect for both studying and relaxing. The facilities are brand new, everything is spotless, and you can really feel the attention to detail in the setup. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a clean, stylish spot with a great atmosphere!

a specialty coffee shop, I tried Tokuma. The pour-over coffee had a great aroma, a smooth acidity, and a sweet aftertaste. The place was quiet and cozy, and the staff was friendly and knowledgeable. I really enjoyed it and will definitely come back!

An interesting place for who loves specialty coffee. Today I drink Tariku Kare from Ethiopia, which has flavour of peach tea. I feel a little bit bitter, and the worker told me that this is a new coffee so maybe the bean's flavour need more time for exploring.
A peaceful and calm atmosphere, friendly staff, and good coffee.
I'm highly recommend this coffee shop for who live in or travel to Saigon, Vietnam.

I almost missed the shop, and there wouldn’t have been a bigger waste.

I was immediately impressed by the cosy and quiet architecture of the place. A great place for the digital nomads out there. However, the real gem was that I discovered an actual artisan coffee shop.

Ngan, the brewer on shift when I came in, was a true artist. She is passionate about coffee and we had an amazing conversation about the craft.

I recommend every coffee enthusiasts out there to give this place a try.

most_relevant.description: I can’t vouch for the food because we just ordered multiple cups of coffee, but this was the start of my specialty coffee journey in Vietnam. They also referred us to other good specialty shops when we asked them. This space is in a good neighborhood with views of the river and huge trees that gives it a really calm vibe. Pricey for the food and hard to get to if you do not have your own vehicle. The table where we were assigned to was dirty and filled with croissant crumbs when we reached, not a welcoming sight when you’re hungry first thing in the morning.

Mosquito repellant was provided too because there were lots of mosquitoes in that area. Some of us still got bitten after spraying.

Food took quite some time to arrive, no hungry and angry man will be delighted at this.

Not sure if we lacked the coffee expertise, this cafe which is known for its coffee didn’t serve coffee tasting to the quality as promised..

I had a matcha tea with oat milk and it wasn't my favorite. It wasn't hot, it was lukewarm. I sat outside which was nice but there were a lot of employees sitting and discussing nearby, which was a bit strange. Overall it was not a great experience for the cost.

Amazing atmosphere, lovely and quiet with strict policies on influencers and people filming.

Coffee was very well brewed, their signature filter coffee really brought out the subtler flavours in the Ethiopian beans we tried.

The Vietnamese “Big Smoke” signature coffee was also great with a good balance of sweetness so you could still taste the difference in the coffee.

Food was good (we had the mushroom toast), but expensive and really took a second place to the coffee… it may have just been that I ordered the wrong thing or was less hungry though… it was very well presented.

Second update 2024: Coffee was excellent as always. The baristas are very knowledgeable but the wait staff could do with some education particularly about the specialty coffees on offer.

Update 2024: I'm updating my review 1 year later. I've upgraded my coffee score from 4 to 5, my service score also from 4 to 5 and my overall review score from 4 to 5.

Not entirely thrilled about having to pay a parking free after already paying for coffee on the pricier end though.

The good thing about this place is delicious coffee! However, the foods are average and can be better, and price is expensive. Over 100k for the coffee latte and almost 200k for a brunch meal. The place is not a bad design with limited seats. Overall, i wish i can give more than 3 stars, but with average food, overprice foods/drink, and slow service.. i give 3 stars. All the best!
